$section Running the Cppad Py Tests$$

$children%bin/get_cppad.sh
	%bin/run_cmake.sh
%$$

$head Configuration$$
You must edit $cref run_cmake.sh$$
to configure Cppad Py for your system.

$head get_cppad.sh$$
The next step is to get a copy of Cppad using the command
$pre
	$$$cref%bin/get_cppad.sh%get_cppad.sh%$$

$head run_cmake.sh$$
The next step is to configure the build using the command
$pre
	$$$cref%bin/run_cmake.sh%run_cmake.sh%$$

$head setup.py$$
The next step is the build the Python cppad_py module using the command
$codep
	python3 setup.py build_ext --inplace
$$
Note that if you change
$cref/python_major_version/run_cmake.sh/python_major_version/$$ to 2,
you will have the use the $code python2$$ command above.

$head check$$
The next step is to check cppad_py on your system using
$codei%
	cd %cmake_binary_dir
	make check
%$$
where $cref/cmake_binary_dir/run_cmake.sh/cmake_binary_dir/$$ is
as specified by $code bin/run_cmake.sh$$.

$head check_swig_xam$$
For $icode lang$$ equal
$code cplusplus$$, $code octave$$, $code perl$$, $code python$$,
$codei%
	make check_swig_xam_%lang%
%$$
only runs a simple test of Swig, for the particular language, on your system.

$head check_lib$$
For $icode lang$$ equal $code cplusplus$$ and $code python$$,
$codei%
	make check_lib_%lang%
%$$
only runs a the tests for the C++ or Python on your system.

$end
